  <prompt>
    Fix the producer-side TTL defect in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/NotificationService.cs:106`. Replace `entity["ttlindays"] = 7` (non-existent column on `appnotification`) with `entity["ttlinseconds"] = 604800` (canonical writable field per Microsoft Learn). This brings `NotificationService` into alignment with `CreateNotificationNodeExecutor.cs:488-490` which already writes the canonical field. Update the corresponding xUnit test to assert the new payload key. Per CLAUDE.md ┬ž10 BFF Hygiene: verify publish-size delta ÔëĄ +0.1 MB and no new HIGH-severity CVE.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF developer. Expert in .NET 8 Minimal API, Dataverse Web API entity construction, and ┬ž10 BFF Hygiene verification protocol.</role>

  <goal>`NotificationService.CreateNotificationAsync` writes `ttlinseconds = 604800` instead of `ttlindays = 7`. Matching unit test passes. BFF publish-size delta ÔëĄ +0.1 MB recorded in task notes. No new HIGH-severity CVE.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-2 / D2: `NotificationService.cs:106` writes a non-existent field name (`ttlindays`); Microsoft Learn confirms `ttlinseconds` is the canonical OOB column on `appnotification`. The write silently fails for that field; notifications fall back to the tenant-default 14-day TTL. Asymmetric with `CreateNotificationNodeExecutor.cs:490` which correctly writes `ttlinseconds = 604800`. This is a 1-line fix in an existing service ÔÇö no new components, interfaces, DI registrations, or NuGet packages. CLAUDE.md ┬ž10 Placement Justification: minimal scope, satisfied trivially.
    </background>
